HEADWORD: Outlive
<hw>Out*live"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Outlived</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Outliving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To live beyond, or
longer than; to survive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They live too long who happiness <qex>outlive</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outliver</ent>⟦br⟧
